Generates and verifies the "tool contracts" doc block (a list of one-paragraph agent-facing contracts) shared across CLAUDE.md, template/CLAUDE.md, and README.md, sourced from each binary's own `--contract` output rather than hand-written prose.

Builds ctx-context, ctx-verify, ctx-scan, ctx-cage, and ctx-brief in debug mode first (`cargo build -q --bin ...`), so the block always reflects current source, not stale binaries; a build failure is a hard error in `--write` mode or emits a single `FAIL:` line in `--check` mode. Each binary's `--contract` text is wrapped as `- **label** — text` and assembled between the literal markers `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED tool-contracts (scripts/gen_tool_contracts.sh --write) -->` / `<!-- END GENERATED tool-contracts -->`; these exact marker strings must exist verbatim in all three docs or the doc is flagged missing/malformed. The block must never be hand-edited between markers — this script is the sole writer.

Two modes: `--write` (default) rewrites the block in place in each doc via an awk pass keyed on the markers; `--check` (used by ctx-verify's `contracts` battery) compares the committed block against a freshly generated one and emits `FAIL: <doc>:1: tool-contracts block is stale — run scripts/gen_tool_contracts.sh --write` on mismatch, without modifying anything. `--check` accumulates failures across all docs and exits nonzero (`FAIL` var) rather than stopping at the first; `--write` exits immediately on the first hard error (missing doc, missing markers, build failure).

Coupling: adding/removing/renaming a contract-bearing binary requires updating the `DOCS` array pairing and the `one_contract` calls here; a mismatch between this script's binary list and the actual `--contract`-implementing binaries silently omits or errors on that entry. `BIN_DIR` is hardcoded to `target/debug` — assumes debug build, not release.